oc:kn_17b05352 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When identifying expansion opportunities" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Watch for expansion signals: approaching seat limits (80%), champion internal advocacy, new department interest, and funding announcements" ;
    oc:hasRationale "These signals indicate the customer is outgrowing their current plan and has both need and organizational momentum for expansion" .

oc:kn_5fa8c795 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When a customer shows churn signals" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For churn risk by reason: price → offer 20% discount for 3 months; not using → free intensive training; competitor → competitive discount + feature commitment; organizational → contract flexibility or pause option" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Tailored save offers address the root cause rather than applying generic discounts that erode value perception" .

oc:kn_762408c8 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When conducting expansion or upsell conversations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Discover customer goals and growth plans → 2. Align expansion value to their objectives → 3. Propose specific recommendation with ROI projection → 4. Close with executive alignment and champion support" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_d09e15c7 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing customer onboarding programs" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Onboarding should follow a 5-phase structure over ~6 weeks: kickoff → implementation → training → launch → handoff, with defined deliverables at each phase" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Structured onboarding ensures consistent time-to-value and prevents gaps that lead to poor adoption" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_e8dd88c9 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building or configuring health scoring models" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Health scores should use a weighted formula across four dimensions: product engagement (40%), relationship (25%), financial (20%), and sentiment (15%)" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Weighting ensures that product usage—the strongest predictor of retention—dominates the score while still capturing relationship and financial signals" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_efc66ed6 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When monitoring customer health scores" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never wait for renewal approaching to engage a customer — health score triggers should drive proactive outreach at score drops below 60 and immediate escalation below 40" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Reactive engagement at renewal time is too late to save at-risk accounts; early intervention dramatically improves retention rates" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_f41951bc a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SuccessIndicator ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When preparing quarterly business reviews" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Key QBR success indicators: user adoption vs target, DAU trends, support ticket volume, NPS score movement, and quantified ROI (hours saved × rate)" ;
    oc:hasRationale "These metrics demonstrate value to the customer's executive sponsor and justify continued investment" .

